---
/* Three hand-drawn SVG graphical abstracts with hover/focus/tap overlays.
 * Each overlay carries a concise Method + Why-it-matters block and a
 * direct DOI CTA. The tap-to-toggle script at the bottom activates only
 * on touch devices so hover remains clean on desktop.
 */
---
<section id="research" class="py-20 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border-t border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mb-12 text-center fade-in">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Featured Research</h2>
      <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-primary rounded-full mx-auto mb-6"></div>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Three pieces of work that shaped how I think about physiological signals, graphs, and
        attention. Each card doubles as its own graphical abstract &mdash;
        <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">hover (or tap) to see the method, why it matters, and a direct link to the paper</span>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

      <!-- Card 1 · Multi-modal MRI + Graph Attention for Stroke -->
      <article class="research-card group relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-white dark:bg-darkCard border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-500 fade-in" data-accent="primary" tabindex="0">
        <div class="relative h-52 overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-500/10 via-sky-500/5 to-blue-600/10">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 210" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-full text-primary p-4"
               aria-label="Graphical abstract: multi-modal MRI merges via graph attention into a stroke lesion mask">
            <defs>
              <marker id="arrowPrimary" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                <path d="M0 0 L10 5 L0 10 z" fill="currentColor" />
              </marker>
            </defs>
            <g transform="translate(18, 30)">
              <rect x="0" y="0"  width="96" height="32" rx="6" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.10" />
              <rect x="0" y="40" width="96" height="32" rx="6" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.18" />
              <rect x="0" y="80" width="96" height="32" rx="6" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.30" />
              <text x="10" y="20"  font-size="11" fill="currentColor" font-weight="700">T1</text>
              <text x="10" y="60"  font-size="11" fill="currentColor" font-weight="700">T2</text>
              <text x="10" y="100" font-size="11" fill="currentColor" font-weight="700">FLAIR</text>
              <text x="0"  y="132" font-size="9"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">multi-modal MRI</text>
            </g>
            <path d="M122 80 L150 80" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrowPrimary)" />
            <g transform="translate(162, 20)">
              <line x1="40" y1="20" x2="80" y2="60"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.35" />
              <line x1="40" y1="20" x2="20" y2="95"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3.5" opacity="0.9" />
              <line x1="80" y1="60" x2="20" y2="95"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" opacity="0.45" />
              <line x1="80" y1="60" x2="95" y2="135" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"   opacity="0.75" />
              <line x1="20" y1="95" x2="95" y2="135" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" opacity="0.4" />
              <line x1="40" y1="20" x2="95" y2="135" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.25" />
              <circle cx="40" cy="20"  r="8"  fill="currentColor" />
              <circle cx="80" cy="60"  r="10" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.85" />
              <circle cx="20" cy="95"  r="12" fill="currentColor" />
              <circle cx="95" cy="135" r="9"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.9" />
              <text x="0" y="175" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">probabilistic graph attention</text>
            </g>
            <path d="M280 80 L310 80" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrowPrimary)" />
            <g transform="translate(320, 35)">
              <path d="M12 6 C30 -2 56 2 64 30 C70 55 56 92 32 92 C8 92 -4 66 2 40 C6 18 6 10 12 6 Z" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
              <ellipse cx="42" cy="44" rx="12" ry="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7" />
              <ellipse cx="42" cy="44" rx="18" ry="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="2 2" opacity="0.5" />
              <text x="-2" y="115" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">lesion mask</text>
            </g>
          </svg>
          <div class="absolute top-3 left-3">
            <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-primary text-white text-[10px] font-bold rounded-full tracking-wide">Neurocomputing · 2025</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2 leading-snug">Graph-Based Multi-Modal MRI with Probabilistic Attention for Stroke Lesion Detection</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            Fuses T1, T2, and FLAIR MRI into a single attention-weighted graph &mdash; sharper lesion maps, in a fraction of the compute.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-overlay absolute inset-0 bg-white/97 dark:bg-darkCard/97 backdrop-blur-sm p-6 flex flex-col opacity-0 translate-y-2 pointer-events-none group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:translate-y-0 group-hover:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-focus-within:translate-y-0 group-focus-within:pointer-events-auto transition-all duration-500 overflow-y-auto">
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-primary mb-1">Method</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3 leading-relaxed">
            Represent each voxel neighborhood as a node and fuse three MRI modalities into a single graph.
            A <span class="font-semibold">probabilistic graph-attention network</span> learns which connections carry
            lesion-relevant evidence &mdash; the uncertainty estimate doubles as an interpretability map for clinicians.
          </p>
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-primary mb-1">Why it matters</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
            In stroke, minutes equal neurons. This approach delivers higher Dice scores than 3D-U-Net baselines
            while generating attention heatmaps that radiologists can sanity-check &mdash; closing the "black-box"
            gap that keeps deep learning out of acute care.
          </p>
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.neucom.2025.131620" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
             class="mt-auto inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full py-2.5 bg-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-secondary transition-colors">
            <i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-2"></i> Read the paper
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Card 2 · EDA-Graph -->
      <article class="research-card group relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-white dark:bg-darkCard border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-500 fade-in" data-accent="emerald" tabindex="0">
        <div class="relative h-52 overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-500/10 via-emerald-500/5 to-teal-500/10">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 210" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-full text-emerald-500 p-4"
               aria-label="Graphical abstract: EDA time series transformed to a graph, mapped to valence and arousal">
            <defs>
              <marker id="arrowEmerald" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                <path d="M0 0 L10 5 L0 10 z" fill="currentColor" />
              </marker>
            </defs>
            <g transform="translate(12, 40)">
              <path d="M0 60 Q12 58 20 55 T40 40 T58 30 Q70 50 85 35 T110 25 Q120 48 135 40"
                    stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" />
              <g stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.25">
                <line x1="0" y1="0"  x2="135" y2="0" />
                <line x1="0" y1="30" x2="135" y2="30" />
                <line x1="0" y1="60" x2="135" y2="60" />
                <line x1="0" y1="90" x2="135" y2="90" />
              </g>
              <text x="0" y="112" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">electrodermal activity</text>
            </g>
            <path d="M160 80 L188 80" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrowEmerald)" />
            <g transform="translate(198, 20)">
              <line x1="20" y1="40" x2="55" y2="18"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" opacity="0.75" />
              <line x1="55" y1="18" x2="90" y2="50"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.45" />
              <line x1="20" y1="40" x2="45" y2="90"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.6" opacity="0.85" />
              <line x1="45" y1="90" x2="90" y2="50"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"   opacity="0.6" />
              <line x1="45" y1="90" x2="85" y2="120" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" opacity="0.5" />
              <line x1="90" y1="50" x2="85" y2="120" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.4" />
              <circle cx="20" cy="40"  r="7"  fill="currentColor" />
              <circle cx="55" cy="18"  r="6"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.85" />
              <circle cx="90" cy="50"  r="8"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.9" />
              <circle cx="45" cy="90"  r="10" fill="currentColor" />
              <circle cx="85" cy="120" r="6"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.85" />
              <text x="0" y="150" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">GSP graph</text>
            </g>
            <path d="M306 80 L330 80" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrowEmerald)" />
            <g transform="translate(335, 30)">
              <rect x="0"  y="0"  width="26" height="26" rx="4" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.35" />
              <rect x="30" y="0"  width="26" height="26" rx="4" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.75" />
              <rect x="0"  y="30" width="26" height="26" rx="4" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.55" />
              <rect x="30" y="30" width="26" height="26" rx="4" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.25" />
              <circle cx="43" cy="13" r="4" fill="white" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
              <text x="0" y="78" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">valence × arousal</text>
            </g>
          </svg>
          <div class="absolute top-3 left-3">
            <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-emerald-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold rounded-full tracking-wide">IEEE JBHI · 2024</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2 leading-snug">EDA-Graph: Graph Signal Processing of Electrodermal Activity for Emotion Detection</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            The first graph-signal-processing pipeline for a biomedical signal &mdash; turns a 1-D sweat trace into a topological feature your classifier can actually see.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-overlay absolute inset-0 bg-white/97 dark:bg-darkCard/97 backdrop-blur-sm p-6 flex flex-col opacity-0 translate-y-2 pointer-events-none group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:translate-y-0 group-hover:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-focus-within:translate-y-0 group-focus-within:pointer-events-auto transition-all duration-500 overflow-y-auto">
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-500 mb-1">Method</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3 leading-relaxed">
            Segment the EDA trace into nodes, weight edges by temporal &amp; phasic similarity, then apply
            <span class="font-semibold">graph Fourier &amp; wavelet transforms</span> to derive spectral descriptors.
            The graph captures nonlinear sweat-gland dynamics that FFT-based baselines flatten out.
          </p>
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-500 mb-1">Why it matters</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
            Emotion recognition in wearables lives or dies by the quality of a single skin-conductance channel.
            EDA-Graph pushed state-of-the-art on the continuous valence &amp; arousal axes while staying cheap enough
            for on-device inference.
          </p>
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1109/JBHI.2024.3405491" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
             class="mt-auto inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full py-2.5 bg-emerald-500 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors">
            <i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-2"></i> Read the paper
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Card 3 · ERG-Graph -->
      <article class="research-card group relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-white dark:bg-darkCard border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-500 fade-in" data-accent="violet" tabindex="0">
        <div class="relative h-52 overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-500/10 via-violet-500/5 to-indigo-500/10">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 210" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-full text-violet-500 p-4"
               aria-label="Graphical abstract: retinal ERG waveform converted to a sparse graph used to classify ASD, ADHD, and typically developing groups">
            <defs>
              <marker id="arrowViolet" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                <path d="M0 0 L10 5 L0 10 z" fill="currentColor" />
              </marker>
            </defs>
            <g transform="translate(14, 50)">
              <ellipse cx="55" cy="40" rx="55" ry="30" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
              <circle cx="55" cy="40" r="16" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.25" />
              <circle cx="55" cy="40" r="7"  fill="currentColor" />
              <path d="M15 52 Q30 48 40 55 L48 30 L58 70 L72 35 L88 50 Q100 52 105 48"
                    stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" fill="none" opacity="0.8" />
              <text x="10" y="95" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">ERG (two flashes)</text>
            </g>
            <path d="M132 90 L160 90" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrowViolet)" />
            <g transform="translate(168, 30)">
              <line x1="20" y1="30" x2="60" y2="15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" opacity="0.75" />
              <line x1="60" y1="15" x2="90" y2="55" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" opacity="0.55" />
              <line x1="20" y1="30" x2="45" y2="85" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.8" opacity="0.85" />
              <line x1="45" y1="85" x2="90" y2="55" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" opacity="0.45" />
              <circle cx="20" cy="30" r="7"  fill="currentColor" />
              <circle cx="60" cy="15" r="6"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.85" />
              <circle cx="90" cy="55" r="8"  fill="currentColor" />
              <circle cx="45" cy="85" r="9"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.9" />
              <text x="0" y="115" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">sparse ERG graph</text>
            </g>
            <path d="M276 90 L304 90" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrowViolet)" />
            <g transform="translate(310, 45)">
              <rect x="0"  y="0"  width="72" height="18" rx="4" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.25" />
              <rect x="0"  y="23" width="72" height="18" rx="4" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7" />
              <rect x="0"  y="46" width="72" height="18" rx="4" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.4" />
              <text x="6"  y="13" font-size="10" fill="currentColor" font-weight="700">TD</text>
              <text x="6"  y="36" font-size="10" fill="white"       font-weight="700">ASD</text>
              <text x="6"  y="59" font-size="10" fill="currentColor" font-weight="700">ADHD</text>
              <text x="-4" y="86" font-size="9"  fill="currentColor" opacity="0.7">classifier</text>
            </g>
          </svg>
          <div class="absolute top-3 left-3">
            <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-violet-500 text-white text-[10px] font-bold rounded-full tracking-wide">Bioengineering · 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2 leading-snug">ERG-Graph: Graph Signal Processing of the Electroretinogram for Neurodevelopmental Disorders</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            A 2-minute retinal recording, rendered as a graph, separates autism and ADHD from typical development with clinical-grade accuracy.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-overlay absolute inset-0 bg-white/97 dark:bg-darkCard/97 backdrop-blur-sm p-6 flex flex-col opacity-0 translate-y-2 pointer-events-none group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:translate-y-0 group-hover:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-focus-within:translate-y-0 group-focus-within:pointer-events-auto transition-all duration-500 overflow-y-auto">
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-violet-500 mb-1">Method</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3 leading-relaxed">
            Extract a-/b-wave peaks from ERG responses at two flash strengths, build a sparse similarity graph
            across waveform landmarks, and feed its graph-Fourier coefficients into a classical classifier.
            The graph discards redundant temporal samples while preserving the diagnostic topology.
          </p>
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-violet-500 mb-1">Why it matters</span>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
            Neurodevelopmental diagnosis today hinges on hours of behavioral assessment. An objective, non-invasive
            retinal biomarker &mdash; cheap enough to run in any vision clinic &mdash; could close diagnostic gaps
            for families who can't reach a specialist.
          </p>
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/bioengineering13040446" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
             class="mt-auto inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full py-2.5 bg-violet-500 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-violet-600 transition-colors">
            <i class="fas fa-file-pdf mr-2"></i> Read the paper
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 text-center text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 fade-in">
      Graphical abstracts are minimalist SVGs I draw by hand to mirror each paper's pipeline. Tap or keyboard-focus any card to flip it.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // Touch devices: tap-to-toggle the overlay. Desktop keeps CSS :hover.
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    const cards = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>(".research-card"));
    if (!cards.length) return;
    const isHover = window.matchMedia("(hover: hover)").matches;
    if (isHover) return;

    cards.forEach((card) => {
      card.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        if ((e.target as HTMLElement).closest("a")) return;
        cards.forEach((c) => c !== card && c.classList.remove("show"));
        card.classList.toggle("show");
      });
    });
    document.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
      if (!(e.target as HTMLElement).closest(".research-card")) {
        cards.forEach((c) => c.classList.remove("show"));
      }
    });
  });
</script>
